    city: 'Wheaton',
    slug: 'wheaton',
    faqs: [
      { q: 'What masonry work is most common in Wheaton?', a: 'Tuckpointing on older brick homes in the historic downtown neighborhoods, chimney repair, and stoop work. Wheaton\'s downtown historic district includes brick commercial and residential buildings with mortar from the 1890s–1930s requiring lime-compatible repair approaches.' },
